\section{Equation Syntax Variants}

\subsection{Inline Mathematics}

Testing inline math with parentheses: \(x^2 + y^2 = z^2\) and more complex \(\sum_{i=1}^{n} a_i = S\).

Testing inline math with dollar signs: $a^2 + b^2 = c^2$ and fractions $\frac{1}{2\pi}$.

Mixed inline expressions: \(\int_0^1 f(x) dx\) versus $\lim_{x \to \infty} \frac{1}{x} = 0$.

Complex inline: \(\begin{pmatrix} a & b \\ c & d \end{pmatrix}\) and $\sqrt{x^2 + y^2}$.

\subsection{Display Mathematics}

Testing display math with brackets:
\[ \sum_{n=0}^{\infty} \frac{x^n}{n!} = e^x \]

Testing display math with double dollars:
$$ \int_{-\infty}^{\infty} e^{-x^2} dx = \sqrt{\pi} $$

Testing display math with equation environment (numbered):
\begin{equation}
\frac{d}{dx}\left[\int_a^x f(t) dt\right] = f(x)
\end{equation}

Testing display math with equation* environment (unnumbered):
\begin{equation*}
\lim_{h \to 0} \frac{f(x+h) - f(x)}{h} = f'(x)
\end{equation*}

\subsection{Multi-line Equations}

Testing align environment (numbered):
\begin{align}
x + y &= 5 \\
2x - 3y &= -4 \\
\therefore x &= 2, \quad y = 3
\end{align}

