\label{fig:solution-curves}
\end{figure}

Figure~\ref{fig:solution-curves} provides a visual representation of the data presented in Table~\ref{tab:numerical-solutions}.

\section{Manual Bibliography Management}
\label{sec:bibliography}

For web-based LaTeX systems where traditional BibTeX processing may be limited, manual bibliography management provides reliable cross-referencing.

\subsection{Creating Reference Lists}
\label{subsec:reference-lists}

References should be created as numbered lists with labels for cross-referencing:

\begin{enumerate}
\item Smith, J.A. (2020). \emph{Mathematical Foundations of Engineering: Theory and Applications}. Academic Press, New York. ISBN: 978-0-12-345678-9.
\label{ref:smith2020}

\item Jones, M.B., Williams, C.D., and Taylor, R.E. (2019). Historical development of engineering mathematics in the digital age. \emph{Journal of Engineering Education}, 45(2):123--145. DOI: 10.1002/jee.2019.45.2.123
\label{ref:jones2019}

\item Brown, P.K. (2021). \emph{Partial Differential Equations in Engineering Applications: Computational Methods and Solutions}. Technical Publications, London. 
\label{ref:brown2021}

\item Wilson, S.L. (2022). Modern approaches to engineering data analysis: Machine learning and statistical methods. \emph{Engineering Statistics Quarterly}, 18(3):67--89.
\label{ref:wilson2022}

\item Chen, L. and Patel, R. (2023). Web-based mathematical document processing: Challenges and solutions. \emph{Computational Mathematics and Engineering}, 12(1):15--32.
\label{ref:chen2023}
\end{enumerate}

\subsection{Referencing the Bibliography}
\label{subsec:referencing}

The foundational work by Smith~\ref{ref:smith2020} provides comprehensive coverage of mathematical principles, while the historical perspective offered by Jones et al.~\ref{ref:jones2019} contextualises modern approaches.

